{
  "$comment": "Dwarf primitives registry. Maps primitive name -> implementation. Scenarios reference primitives by name only. Adding a primitive is a code change: drop a Python module under primitives/<family>/, register it here, add a params_schema, regenerate docs/primitives-reference.md. Pasted scenarios cannot add primitives. The 'primitives' map is empty in this slice; primitives populate in Slices 7, 12, 13, and 14.",
  "entry_schema": {
    "$comment": "Documents the shape each entry in 'primitives' must take. Not validated by the runner today; serves as an authoring reference and seed for the loader added in Slice 7.",
    "class": "string. Name of the class within that module implementing the primitive interface.",
    "family": "string. One of: setup | load | probe | assertion | fault | teardown.",
    "module": "string. Python import path of the module providing the primitive.",
    "params_schema": "string. Path (relative to dwarf/) to a JSON Schema validating this primitive's parameter object inside a scenario's primitive reference.",
    "runtimes": "array of strings. Execution tiers this primitive can run under: library | single-node | devnet.",
    "supports": "array of strings. Cardano implementations this primitive can drive: cardano-node | amaru.",
    "version": "string. Semver of the primitive itself. Bump on behavior change so that bundles record which version produced the result."
  },
